author: David Brennan
title: Benjamin Netanyahu Will Not Need to Self-Isolate After Aide Tests Positive for Coronavirus, Office Suggests
description: Rivka Paluch—Netanyahu's adviser on ultra-Orthodox affairs—tested positive after her husband was hospitalized with the virus.
content:
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu will not have to self-isolate for 14 days after one of his aides tested positive for COVID-19 coronavirus, according to officials in his office.
